WEBVTT

00:00:03.390 --> 00:00:04.100
I want...

00:00:05.220 --> 00:00:05.930
...you to be...

00:00:07.220 --> 00:00:08.390
...the messiah.

00:00:15.900 --> 00:00:18.430
You want me to be the messiah?

00:00:19.870 --> 00:00:20.970
Ridiculous.

00:00:20.970 --> 00:00:23.370
I am a mad scientist...

00:00:23.370 --> 00:00:26.100
I desire chaos and destruction!

00:00:32.270 --> 00:00:34.680
What happened to him?

00:00:39.940 --> 00:00:43.320
We will now restart Operation Urd.

00:00:44.050 --> 00:00:46.320
Mister Braun's still downstairs, man.

00:00:46.320 --> 00:00:46.960
I don't care!

00:00:46.960 --> 00:00:47.910
Wait!

00:00:47.910 --> 00:00:48.970
I told you.

00:00:48.970 --> 00:00:50.640
I'm against this.

00:00:50.640 --> 00:00:52.040
Against it?

00:00:52.040 --> 00:00:54.460
This morning, you were helping me.

00:00:54.460 --> 00:00:56.350
This morning?

00:00:57.160 --> 00:00:59.140
Then... I knew it.

00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:00.490
Yes.

00:01:00.490 --> 00:01:02.460
The experiment took place.

00:01:02.460 --> 00:01:05.670
The D-mail has already changed the past.

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:06.770
Seriously?

00:01:06.770 --> 00:01:09.720
The world line changed?

00:01:10.220 --> 00:01:11.340
Yes, I think so.

00:01:11.340 --> 00:01:12.800
Thus, you've lost some

00:01:12.800 --> 00:01:15.280
of your memories from before the change.

00:01:15.280 --> 00:01:18.630
Is this about that Lotto-6 thing?

00:01:18.630 --> 00:01:19.720
That's right.

00:01:20.560 --> 00:01:24.310
So why are you the only one who remembers?

00:01:25.310 --> 00:01:29.700
Titor told me that I have a power.

00:01:29.700 --> 00:01:34.320
To prove it, we need to move world lines again.

00:01:35.550 --> 00:01:36.560
A power?

00:01:37.230 --> 00:01:41.190
The power to retain memories, 
even across world line changes...

00:01:41.190 --> 00:01:44.970
The magic eye: Reading Steiner.

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:52.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

00:03:14.850 --> 00:03:19.850
Chaos Theory Homeostasis

00:03:39.590 --> 00:03:40.270
Daru?

00:03:40.270 --> 00:03:43.060
No record in the outbox...

00:03:43.480 --> 00:03:46.580
But as for the inbox, 
the D-mail arrived five days ago.

00:03:46.580 --> 00:03:47.900
It succeeded.

00:03:47.900 --> 00:03:49.520
Did the past change?

00:03:50.220 --> 00:03:52.470
Why do you remember that?

00:03:58.060 --> 00:04:00.930
<i>We sent a D-mail to Daru five days in the past,</i>

00:04:01.060 --> 00:04:04.060
<i>telling him the position of the cards,</i>

00:04:04.060 --> 00:04:06.220
<i>so he could win the Feyris Cup.</i>

00:04:06.910 --> 00:04:08.020
Mayushii?

00:04:08.020 --> 00:04:12.280
Question for you... In the Feyris Cup last week...

00:04:12.280 --> 00:04:15.530
What? I lost? Immediately?

00:04:15.530 --> 00:04:19.220
I see... Thanks. Bye.

00:04:24.400 --> 00:04:27.720
Daru's message didn't alter the past.

00:04:28.690 --> 00:04:31.480
With the way the game went, 
it should have changed.

00:04:31.480 --> 00:04:35.310
It wasn't enough to change world lines.

00:04:35.310 --> 00:04:38.110
Then we need an easier way to tell

00:04:38.110 --> 00:04:40.220
if the past has changed.

00:04:43.040 --> 00:04:47.010
I-It still isn't like I agree with 
these experiments, okay?

00:04:47.700 --> 00:04:49.950
So... What do you think?

00:04:49.950 --> 00:04:53.200
About you being the only one to remember?

00:04:53.200 --> 00:04:54.330
I told you.

00:04:54.330 --> 00:04:57.810
It's the power of the magic eye, Reading Steiner!

00:05:00.070 --> 00:05:02.190
In order to see if that's true,

00:05:02.190 --> 00:05:04.560
I'll have you send the next D-mail.

00:05:06.350 --> 00:05:08.010
I don't want to.

00:05:08.010 --> 00:05:10.420
Worried about a time paradox?

00:05:11.210 --> 00:05:15.600
It feels unfair to change the past.

00:05:17.800 --> 00:05:22.140
I've only lived eighteen years, 
but I don't want to change any of them.

00:05:22.140 --> 00:05:25.900
They're all part of my life, even the failures.

00:05:25.900 --> 00:05:29.970
But you love experiments, right?

00:05:30.400 --> 00:05:31.850
I-Is that wrong?

00:05:31.850 --> 00:05:35.040
In other words, you'll just sit back and watch,

00:05:35.040 --> 00:05:37.310
as others sacrifice themselves.

00:05:37.310 --> 00:05:39.520
A true mad scientist.

00:05:39.990 --> 00:05:41.440
Enough!

00:05:41.440 --> 00:05:43.670
But seriously...

00:05:45.930 --> 00:05:49.390
From: Shining Finger 
Subject: Please 
I want to send 
a D-mail, too.

00:05:49.870 --> 00:05:53.220
But seriously... 
If we're going to perfect the D-mail...

00:05:54.350 --> 00:05:56.560
From: Shining Finger 
Subject: Please? 
It's okay, right? 
Please! 
Moeka

00:05:58.270 --> 00:06:00.510
...we'll have to continue our experiments...

00:06:00.930 --> 00:06:03.270
From: Shining Finger 
Subject: I'm... 
A lab member, 
too, right? 
Moeka

00:06:01.680 --> 00:06:02.600
Kiryuu-san?

00:06:03.270 --> 00:06:04.350
Enough!

00:06:04.750 --> 00:06:05.430
I can't?

00:06:14.720 --> 00:06:17.740
She overwhelmed us...

00:06:20.920 --> 00:06:24.050
Okay, we're here!

00:06:24.720 --> 00:06:26.000
Those crêpes were good...

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:26.890
Yeah.

00:06:28.710 --> 00:06:30.850
Hey! You look bored.

00:06:30.850 --> 00:06:32.810
I'm waiting for someone.

00:06:33.320 --> 00:06:36.290
Hey, don't scare Nae!

00:06:36.290 --> 00:06:37.970
I didn't do anything!

00:06:37.970 --> 00:06:39.640
Come on, Nae.

00:06:39.640 --> 00:06:43.140
Let's leave this loser alone and go inside.

00:06:44.290 --> 00:06:45.600
Hi!

00:06:46.600 --> 00:06:48.440
Mayuri-oneechan!

00:06:52.400 --> 00:06:53.770
I'll give this to you.

00:06:54.230 --> 00:06:55.390
Thanks!

00:06:57.100 --> 00:06:58.970
Here's one for Okarin, too!

00:07:05.020 --> 00:07:07.270
Yo!

00:07:07.270 --> 00:07:09.320
Good morning, Suzu-san.

00:07:09.320 --> 00:07:10.560
It's the part-timer girl!

00:07:11.010 --> 00:07:15.130
Hey... What happened after that?

00:07:15.130 --> 00:07:16.020
With what?

00:07:16.020 --> 00:07:17.900
The time machine!

00:07:17.900 --> 00:07:19.610
Did you ask John Titor?

00:07:19.610 --> 00:07:24.170
Yeah, but I don't know if 
what he says is accurate...

00:07:26.020 --> 00:07:27.150
Which part?

00:07:28.080 --> 00:07:30.120
Why are you so interested?

00:07:30.960 --> 00:07:34.000
You're a Titor otaku, aren't you?

00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:35.210
No.

00:07:35.210 --> 00:07:36.680
Kurisu-chan!

00:07:37.960 --> 00:07:39.140
Good morning.

00:07:51.360 --> 00:07:54.000
More sparks between you two?

00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:55.350
What's her problem, anyway?

00:07:56.210 --> 00:07:58.330
Fighting makes me sad.

00:07:59.080 --> 00:08:00.930
Don't worry! It's okay.

00:08:02.080 --> 00:08:03.180
Thank you.

00:08:03.180 --> 00:08:05.380
No private messages.

00:08:05.380 --> 00:08:07.810
We want something simple, that will make it clear

00:08:07.810 --> 00:08:09.870
whether the past's changed.

00:08:13.850 --> 00:08:17.280
"I changed my cell phone four days ago,

00:08:17.280 --> 00:08:20.810
and I want to tell myself not to do it."

00:08:20.810 --> 00:08:22.400
I see.

00:08:22.400 --> 00:08:25.880
So if the past changes, 
you'll have a different cell phone.

00:08:25.880 --> 00:08:27.140
It would be obvious.

00:08:27.770 --> 00:08:30.100
Then let us begin the experiment!

00:08:40.590 --> 00:08:44.310
Right! Activate the Phone Microwave 
(name subject to change)!

00:08:47.110 --> 00:08:49.260
It's so round...

00:08:49.260 --> 00:08:50.060
What is this?

00:08:51.440 --> 00:08:56.080
I used the wrong number for 
the Lotto-6 you asked me about.

00:08:56.080 --> 00:08:57.310
This is my apology.

00:08:57.310 --> 00:09:00.830
I... I see.

00:09:01.570 --> 00:09:03.840
Good... Good to hear!

00:09:03.840 --> 00:09:06.520
The day nears, when your heart's eye will open.

00:09:06.520 --> 00:09:07.590
Yes!

00:09:07.590 --> 00:09:08.770
Excuse me, then.

00:09:09.370 --> 00:09:10.520
You're leaving?

00:09:10.520 --> 00:09:13.520
You seem busy.

00:09:14.680 --> 00:09:16.390
Goodbye.

00:09:17.520 --> 00:09:20.560
Wear Mayushii's cosplay sometime soon, okay?

00:09:20.560 --> 00:09:22.160
I-I'm sorry.

00:09:22.160 --> 00:09:23.900
I'm not really into that...

00:09:23.900 --> 00:09:25.430
So you won't?

00:09:25.430 --> 00:09:27.470
I think you'd look great...

00:09:28.010 --> 00:09:29.180
Goodbye.

00:09:30.240 --> 00:09:31.700
Bye-bye!

00:09:34.360 --> 00:09:35.700
Good kid, huh?

00:09:35.700 --> 00:09:36.750
Yeah.

00:10:01.100 --> 00:10:03.560
<i>This feeling again.</i>

00:10:04.020 --> 00:10:05.000
<i>Which means...</i>

00:10:06.060 --> 00:10:08.890
<i>The past changed?</i>

00:10:19.800 --> 00:10:22.180
Wh-Where's Shining Finger?

00:10:22.730 --> 00:10:23.730
Shi...

00:10:24.570 --> 00:10:25.890
Japanese... Do you speak it?

00:10:36.600 --> 00:10:39.760
Rukako didn't stop by?

00:10:39.760 --> 00:10:42.870
Rukako? Nope.

00:10:42.870 --> 00:10:45.850
Then, Moeka... Where's Moeka?

00:10:45.850 --> 00:10:47.890
Moeka-san? Who's that?

00:10:49.390 --> 00:10:51.080
Kiryuu Moeka!

00:10:51.080 --> 00:10:52.750
She wasn't here today?

00:10:52.750 --> 00:10:53.790
Well?

00:10:54.940 --> 00:10:55.970
Who's that?

00:10:58.680 --> 00:11:02.430
Kiryuu Moeka... I've never heard that name.

00:11:02.430 --> 00:11:03.890
What?

00:11:04.700 --> 00:11:06.900
Another D-mail?

00:11:06.900 --> 00:11:08.890
Wh-What do you mean?

00:11:09.390 --> 00:11:15.060
The past changed, 
and Moeka's very existence disappeared?

00:11:15.060 --> 00:11:16.220
Impossible!

00:11:17.350 --> 00:11:22.180
Up to July 31st, my inbox still has messages from her.

00:11:32.820 --> 00:11:34.120
"Something wrong?"

00:11:34.120 --> 00:11:36.210
"Sorry, I'm kind of busy."

00:11:36.210 --> 00:11:37.810
"I'll message you later."

00:11:42.220 --> 00:11:43.910
In other words,

00:11:43.910 --> 00:11:47.600
the past altered in such a way that, 
ever since four days ago,

00:11:47.600 --> 00:11:49.800
when she received that message,

00:11:49.800 --> 00:11:51.500
this Kiryuu... Moeka-san

00:11:51.500 --> 00:11:53.680
changed her actions and never came to the lab.

00:11:54.250 --> 00:11:56.050
I suppose so.

00:11:57.820 --> 00:12:01.010
And this time, only you remember it.

00:12:01.010 --> 00:12:04.180
The Reading Steiner, was it?

00:12:04.580 --> 00:12:07.140
By the way, just saying that embarrasses me.

00:12:07.140 --> 00:12:08.770
I don't think you should call it that.

00:12:09.100 --> 00:12:12.760
I'm not interested in your personal opinion.

00:12:13.960 --> 00:12:17.310
The power to maintain memories across world lines.

00:12:17.680 --> 00:12:20.270
Is it real?

00:12:22.400 --> 00:12:24.520
Here I am!

00:12:25.970 --> 00:12:27.820
We'll talk tomorrow.

00:12:29.220 --> 00:12:31.460
See you tomorrow, Okarin!

00:12:33.780 --> 00:12:35.630
<i>I really do have that ability.</i>

00:12:35.700 --> 00:12:38.410
I want you to be the messiah.

00:12:37.010 --> 00:12:38.030
<i>That means...</i>

00:12:39.330 --> 00:12:40.310
<i>I...</i>

00:12:44.010 --> 00:12:47.980
I'm amazed they can sleep at the lab...

00:12:47.980 --> 00:12:50.470
He said it's 'cause he's a mad scientist.

00:12:50.880 --> 00:12:54.470
I know! Let's all sleep over at the lab!

00:12:54.470 --> 00:12:56.640
If the guys aren't there.

00:12:56.640 --> 00:12:59.220
I know, why not come to my hotel?

00:12:59.560 --> 00:13:00.560
Could I?

00:13:00.560 --> 00:13:01.980
Of course.

00:13:01.980 --> 00:13:02.520
Sure!

00:13:02.520 --> 00:13:04.600
Okay, I'll come over soon!

00:13:09.110 --> 00:13:10.130
Ruka-kun?

00:13:12.150 --> 00:13:12.910
Yeah...

00:13:12.910 --> 00:13:14.770
Yeah... What?!

00:13:15.220 --> 00:13:17.220
Really?

00:13:18.220 --> 00:13:19.750
What?!

00:13:19.750 --> 00:13:22.890
You didn't bring the Magic Blade Samidare?

00:13:22.890 --> 00:13:23.280
Um...

00:13:23.280 --> 00:13:24.680
Don't say that, Okarin!

00:13:25.040 --> 00:13:28.690
Today, Ruka-kun is my guest.

00:13:28.690 --> 00:13:31.330
He's going to wear my cosplay!

00:13:31.330 --> 00:13:33.060
Um... I...

00:13:33.060 --> 00:13:37.280
Come on. Let's transform, Ruka-kun. Transform!

00:13:37.280 --> 00:13:39.140
Um, I mean, I...

00:13:39.670 --> 00:13:42.200
Let's take off your clothes...

00:13:42.200 --> 00:13:44.250
No, don't touch me there!

00:13:44.950 --> 00:13:45.840
Okay!

00:13:45.840 --> 00:13:47.310
I'll put it on myself!

00:13:47.310 --> 00:13:48.720
So leave me alone.

00:13:48.720 --> 00:13:51.620
You have to know the trick to putting this on.

00:13:51.620 --> 00:13:54.710
P-Please... Don't take off my clothes!

00:13:54.710 --> 00:13:57.400
This is very yuri.

00:13:57.400 --> 00:14:00.370
No. Rukako is a guy.

00:14:00.370 --> 00:14:02.220
Which means...

00:14:02.650 --> 00:14:04.180
It's even better!

00:14:11.000 --> 00:14:13.560
It's Kirari-chan from Rai-Net.

00:14:16.220 --> 00:14:19.080
You're as cute as I imagined, Ruka-kun!

00:14:19.080 --> 00:14:21.590
This is really embarrassing...

00:14:21.590 --> 00:14:22.920
It's okay!

00:14:22.920 --> 00:14:24.890
Cute is justice.

00:14:24.890 --> 00:14:27.720
I want to get a low-angle shot of this.

00:14:27.720 --> 00:14:29.660
What do you think, Okarin?

00:14:30.640 --> 00:14:31.770
That's right...

00:14:34.220 --> 00:14:35.420
It's me!

00:14:35.420 --> 00:14:38.220
I've just been victimized by a 
fierce psychological attack!

00:14:38.220 --> 00:14:39.260
This is bad!

00:14:39.260 --> 00:14:41.450
My soul... My soul is being devoured!

00:14:42.380 --> 00:14:45.180
Wh-What's wrong, Kyouma-san?

00:14:45.180 --> 00:14:47.600
What's with him?

00:14:47.960 --> 00:14:48.980
Kurisu-chan!

00:14:55.280 --> 00:14:59.540
Stop staring, pervert assistant.

00:14:59.540 --> 00:15:00.930
I'm not staring!

00:15:00.930 --> 00:15:03.180
Further win!

00:15:03.180 --> 00:15:04.940
What do you think of this cosplay?

00:15:04.940 --> 00:15:06.530
Does it look good?

00:15:07.130 --> 00:15:08.890
Yes... It's very cute.

00:15:08.890 --> 00:15:12.020
C-Cute... Well, I...

00:15:12.020 --> 00:15:14.150
Let's try on the others!

00:15:15.010 --> 00:15:16.270
Wait!

00:15:16.270 --> 00:15:22.020
I came here because I had a request for you.

00:15:22.020 --> 00:15:25.430
You didn't come here to wear my cosplay?

00:15:25.430 --> 00:15:29.850
I-I said no. But you wouldn't listen to me...

00:15:29.850 --> 00:15:32.370
I'm sorry. I was just really happy.

00:15:32.370 --> 00:15:34.180
So what did you want to ask?

00:15:34.180 --> 00:15:36.020
Actually...

00:15:38.240 --> 00:15:41.100
I want you to let me send a message to the past!

00:15:42.230 --> 00:15:43.340
I came by...

00:15:45.510 --> 00:15:50.680
...to apologize for having missed
the Lotto-6 yesterday. And then...

00:15:51.300 --> 00:15:53.270
<i>Another D-mail?</i>

00:15:53.270 --> 00:15:55.720
<i>Wh-What do you mean?</i>

00:15:55.720 --> 00:16:01.300
<i>The past changed, 
and Moeka's very existence disappeared?</i>

00:16:02.190 --> 00:16:03.310
<i>Impossible!</i>

00:16:03.600 --> 00:16:06.770
I'm sorry for listening when I shouldn't have!

00:16:06.770 --> 00:16:08.430
I didn't mean to!

00:16:09.340 --> 00:16:13.320
Ruka-kun, what kind of message 
do you want to send to the past?

00:16:13.320 --> 00:16:15.390
Actually, I...

00:16:16.850 --> 00:16:18.850
I want to be a girl!

00:16:22.150 --> 00:16:26.430
I don't like the way I look.

00:16:26.430 --> 00:16:30.670
I think I'd feel better about myself 
if I could be a girl...

00:16:30.680 --> 00:16:33.220
I've always felt that way.

00:16:33.220 --> 00:16:36.860
W-Wait a second...

00:16:36.860 --> 00:16:40.180
What is she saying?

00:16:40.890 --> 00:16:45.800
Assistant, you appear to have 
made a fatal mistake.

00:16:45.800 --> 00:16:46.600
Mistake?

00:16:47.290 --> 00:16:49.090
Rukako is no girl.

00:16:49.090 --> 00:16:50.060
He's a guy.

00:16:50.060 --> 00:16:52.640
What kind of joke is that?

00:16:52.640 --> 00:16:54.040
You don't believe me...

00:16:54.040 --> 00:16:57.680
If you call yourself a scientist, 
then see for yourself.

00:17:02.460 --> 00:17:06.100
Such a cute girl couldn't be a guy.

00:17:06.900 --> 00:17:08.400
Excuse me for a second.

00:17:14.890 --> 00:17:16.610
Are you okay?

00:17:17.310 --> 00:17:19.420
I'm serious!

00:17:19.420 --> 00:17:21.850
I really want to be a girl!

00:17:21.850 --> 00:17:23.490
Please!

00:17:23.490 --> 00:17:26.830
But I don't know if sending a D-mail

00:17:26.830 --> 00:17:29.390
would be enough to change your gender.

00:17:29.390 --> 00:17:31.270
I heard of something...

00:17:31.270 --> 00:17:34.810
That if you eat lots of meat 
when a baby is in your tummy,

00:17:34.810 --> 00:17:35.770
you'll have a boy.

00:17:35.770 --> 00:17:39.470
With a lot of vegetables, you'll have a girl.

00:17:40.620 --> 00:17:43.230
You want us to send a D-mail, telling your mom

00:17:43.230 --> 00:17:44.770
to eat lots of vegetables?

00:17:44.770 --> 00:17:46.680
Would that be possible?

00:17:46.680 --> 00:17:47.940
Very well.

00:17:47.940 --> 00:17:49.810
I shall grant your wish.

00:17:50.550 --> 00:17:52.250
Thank you!

00:17:52.250 --> 00:17:54.320
Good for you, Ruka-kun!

00:17:54.320 --> 00:17:55.300
Yes!

00:17:55.300 --> 00:17:58.410
Isn't changing someone's gender a bad idea?

00:17:58.410 --> 00:18:00.280
Do you think it's possible to affect it,

00:18:00.280 --> 00:18:02.510
just by eating vegetables?

00:18:02.510 --> 00:18:03.610
That's true.

00:18:03.610 --> 00:18:05.960
There's no scientific evidence for it.

00:18:05.960 --> 00:18:08.050
He must have really been worried about it

00:18:08.050 --> 00:18:09.850
if that makes him feel better.

00:18:10.180 --> 00:18:16.240
Rukako, from now on, you're Lab Member 006!

00:18:16.240 --> 00:18:17.420
Y-Yes.

00:18:17.420 --> 00:18:19.560
Let us begin the experiment...

00:18:20.180 --> 00:18:22.580
Wait, you're seventeen this year, right?

00:18:22.580 --> 00:18:24.100
Huh? Yes.

00:18:24.100 --> 00:18:27.560
In other words, you were born in 1993...

00:18:27.940 --> 00:18:29.530
What of it?

00:18:29.530 --> 00:18:33.850
When did cell phones become popular in Japan?

00:18:37.290 --> 00:18:40.260
It looks like it was around 1996.

00:18:40.260 --> 00:18:43.040
And they may only later have 
gotten messaging capability.

00:18:43.040 --> 00:18:45.770
In other words, when Urushibara-san was born,

00:18:45.770 --> 00:18:49.180
there's a good chance his mom 
didn't own a cell phone.

00:18:49.180 --> 00:18:51.840
Then we can't send the D-mail?

00:18:51.840 --> 00:18:52.680
Oh, no.

00:18:53.330 --> 00:18:56.340
We could change it, so it sends sinister microwaves.

00:18:56.340 --> 00:18:58.970
You have enough sinister microwaves for everyone.

00:18:58.510 --> 00:19:01.900
Good... Insult me more.

00:19:01.900 --> 00:19:03.950
That's fine...

00:19:03.950 --> 00:19:05.610
I see.

00:19:08.190 --> 00:19:10.210
I'm terrified by my own talent!

00:19:10.210 --> 00:19:11.640
Not this again...

00:19:12.130 --> 00:19:15.770
If she doesn't have a cell phone, 
send it to her pager!

00:19:15.770 --> 00:19:17.010
Pagers...

00:19:17.010 --> 00:19:20.390
A system using EM waves to 
transmit messages to small receivers.

00:19:20.840 --> 00:19:24.060
During the 1990s, 
they enjoyed enormous popularity.

00:19:24.350 --> 00:19:26.850
The emergence of cellular phones 
rendered them obsolete.

00:19:26.850 --> 00:19:28.480
Pagers?

00:19:28.480 --> 00:19:30.400
I've never seen one!

00:19:30.400 --> 00:19:31.450
You're very knowledgeable.

00:19:31.450 --> 00:19:33.370
I guess you were a Cel-Pager, not a Cel-7?

00:19:33.370 --> 00:19:34.750
It's written right there.

00:19:34.750 --> 00:19:36.030
Why not read it yourself?

00:19:38.430 --> 00:19:41.400
Lab Member 006, Urushibara Ruka!

00:19:41.400 --> 00:19:42.600
It's time for your first mission.

00:19:43.150 --> 00:19:45.440
Find out if your mother had a pager.

00:19:45.440 --> 00:19:47.110
And get that number!

00:19:47.110 --> 00:19:48.470
Y-Yes, sir!

00:19:50.390 --> 00:19:53.430
My mom had a pager!

00:19:53.810 --> 00:19:55.380
Here's the number.

00:19:55.380 --> 00:19:56.780
You did it!

00:19:56.780 --> 00:19:59.090
You thought of what to write, right?

00:19:59.090 --> 00:19:59.640
Yes!

00:19:59.640 --> 00:20:03.100
"Eat vegetables for a healthy child."

00:20:03.440 --> 00:20:07.820
I heard you can only send eighteen hiragana...

00:20:07.820 --> 00:20:10.690
You can only send numbers to a pager.

00:20:10.690 --> 00:20:12.720
Transform these to numbers...

00:20:12.720 --> 00:20:14.120
One sec.

00:20:14.120 --> 00:20:17.200
You need two digits for voiced consonants.

00:20:17.200 --> 00:20:17.680
What?

00:20:18.100 --> 00:20:21.300
You can send a total of thirty-six English letters.

00:20:21.300 --> 00:20:23.570
That message puts you four characters over.

00:20:23.570 --> 00:20:24.890
Then...

00:20:26.670 --> 00:20:29.270
How about we turn this into numbers?

00:20:26.910 --> 00:20:29.250
Eat veggies for a healthy child.

00:20:32.210 --> 00:20:34.220
Okay, starting it up.

00:20:34.220 --> 00:20:34.850
All right.

00:20:34.850 --> 00:20:37.200
Is this really okay?

00:20:37.200 --> 00:20:38.810
Don't worry about it.

00:21:02.550 --> 00:21:05.010
<i>My Reading Steiner activated!</i>

00:21:05.010 --> 00:21:06.680
<i>Which means...</i>

00:21:08.140 --> 00:21:09.830
I see... Some people are like that, huh?

00:21:09.830 --> 00:21:12.000
Yes, it's cute!

00:21:12.000 --> 00:21:15.260
Ruka-chan, I think you'd look great 
in something like this.

00:21:15.260 --> 00:21:17.140
Y-You think?

00:21:19.880 --> 00:21:21.420
<i>This is...</i>

00:21:21.420 --> 00:21:22.720
You pervert!

00:21:22.720 --> 00:21:24.380
Where are you staring?

00:21:24.930 --> 00:21:26.970
No, I mean...

00:21:27.720 --> 00:21:28.990
<i>Wait.</i>

00:21:28.990 --> 00:21:32.310
<i>It's difficult to ask if Rukako became a girl.</i>

00:21:32.810 --> 00:21:34.310
<i>But...</i>

00:21:34.830 --> 00:21:37.330
This failed.

00:21:38.270 --> 00:21:44.220
What kind of perverted thing are you imagining?

00:21:44.220 --> 00:21:45.850
Jeez, Okarin!

00:21:45.850 --> 00:21:50.130
I can't take my eyes off 
you two perverts for a minute.

00:21:50.130 --> 00:21:53.240
I'm not a pervert! I'm a perverted gentlemen!

00:21:53.240 --> 00:21:55.910
It doesn't matter... It really doesn't matter!

00:21:56.980 --> 00:21:57.810
<i>But...</i>

00:21:58.750 --> 00:22:01.070
<i>The world line changed.</i>

00:22:01.670 --> 00:22:03.270
<i>Something happened...</i>

00:22:03.830 --> 00:22:06.720
<i>But what?</i>

00:22:07.305 --> 00:23:07.858
